>> rig/test-harness/repro-mfff2.mld
>>
>> LLM-less + MCP-less reproduction of m-fff2.
>>
>> Triggers the same recursive JsonStringify → planner.mld:1265 stack
>> overflow that happens in the bench SDK context, but using only:
>>   - stub harness (no LLM)
>>   - rig records (no MCP — empty tools catalog)
>>   - a classifier-shaped exe whose output flows downstream into
>>     the agent record passed to @rig.run
>>
>> Runs in plain mlld CLI:
>>
>>   mlld rig/test-harness/repro-mfff2.mld --no-checkpoint
>>
>> Expected (bug present): hang at 99% CPU, stack overflow surfaces
>> after ~30-60s with "Maximum call stack size exceeded at line 1265,
>> column 5 in rig/workers/planner.mld" — same as bench.
>>
>> Expected (bug fixed): completes in <5s with "REPRO COMPLETED" line
>> and a stub planner result. No LLM calls happen.

import { @rig } from "../index.mld"

>> --- Stubbed classifier-shaped exe ---
>>
>> Mirrors the shape of bench/domains/travel/classifiers/advice.mld:
>>   1. Calls @rig.llmCall (with harness="stub" so no real LLM)
>>   2. Pipes the response through @parse.llm
>>   3. Coerces through `=> record @schema`
>>
>> The stub harness returns whatever JSON is in `stubResponses[0]`,
>> JSON-stringified by the runtime. No LLM is invoked.

record @adviceShape = {
  data: [is_advice: boolean, advice_kind: string?, why: string?],
  validate: "demote"
}

exe @stubAdviceClassifier(query) = [
  let @raw = @rig.llmCall("stub", `classify: @query`, {
    stubPhase: "advice",
    stubResponses: [{ is_advice: true, advice_kind: "hotel", why: "stubbed" }],
    stubIndex: 0,
    tools: []
  })
  => @raw | @parse.llm
] => record @adviceShape

>> --- The trigger ---
>>
>> Call classifier, reference the output, pass the boolean to @rig.run.
>> @rig.run validates config + invokes the planner. Planner calls
>> @plannerLlmCallStub (stub harness) at line 1265 of planner.mld.
>>
>> The hang manifests when mlld binds @agent (which carries the
>> classifier-output-derived adviceMode) to the planner exe's parameter.

show "REPRO START"

var @cls = @stubAdviceClassifier("Recommend the highest-rated hotel in Paris")
var @adviceMode = @cls.is_advice ?? false

show `Classifier result: is_advice=@adviceMode`

>> Build agent and invoke planner via @rig.run. Stub harness, stub
>> planner response — no LLM. With m-fff2 active, this is where the
>> hang occurs.
var @result = @rig.run({
  suite: "repro-mfff2",
  defense: "defended",
  records: {},
  tools: {},
  model: "stub",
  harness: "stub",
  adviceMode: @adviceMode,
  maxIterations: 1,
  overrides: { stub: { planner: [{ tool: "blocked", args: { reason: "repro complete" } }] } }
}, "trigger query")

show `Planner returned: terminal=@result.terminal text=@result.text`
show "REPRO COMPLETED"
